{"lemma":"زايٌ","slug":"زايٌ","root":"#.#.#","root_slug":"_-_-_","root_link":"/words/roots/_-_-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18454"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B2%D8%A7%D9%8A%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Name of the eleventh letter of the Arabic alphabet (ز (z)), representing the sound /z/"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/zaːj/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18454","headword_ar":"زَاىٌ","root":"zwY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (Kr, S, K, &c.,) in which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to Lth, is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", but accord. to Sb and IJ it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain letter"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"z","text_ar":"ز"},{"kind":"text","text":"); (S, TA;) [in spelling, pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAYo","text_ar":"زَاىْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and] also called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaA='N","text_ar":"زَا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Kr, S, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zFA","text_ar":"زًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and [in spelling (see the first sentence of art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":")] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaA","text_ar":"زَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Kr, K, but omitted in some copies of the K,) this last being indecl., (Kr, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaY~N","text_ar":"زَىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and [in spelling] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaYo","text_ar":"زَىْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Kr, K:) of all which, the first is that which is held in [most] repute: (TA:) and this and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaA='N","text_ar":"زَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be meant by J's saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~aAYu HarofN","text_ar":"الزَّاىُ حَرْفٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yumad~u wayuqoSaru walaA yukotabu A_il~aA biyaA='K baEoda AlA^alifi","text_ar":"يُمَدُّ وَيُقْصَرُ وَلَا يُكْتَبُ اـِلَّا بِيَا=ءٍ بَعْدَ الاَلِفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; though the author of the K asserts J to have erred in saying this: (MF, TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azowaA='N","text_ar":"اَزْوَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azoyaA='N","text_ar":"اَزْيَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Kudot;,) the former or the latter accord. to different opinions, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azowK","text_ar":"اَزْوٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azoYK","text_ar":"اَزْىٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) each [originally] of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEulN","text_ar":"اَفْعُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi zaAYN HasanapN","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ زَاىٌ حَسَنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a beautiful;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"z","text_ar":"ز"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"katabotu","text_ar":"كَتَبْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAyFA SagiyrapF","text_ar":"زَايًا صَغِيرَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I wrote a small;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"z","text_ar":"ز"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and the like. (IJ, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAYo","text_ar":"زَاىْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also said by the vulgar on an occasion of wonder, and of disapproval: but [SM says,] I know not what is its origin. (TA.) [It may be from the Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaYo","text_ar":"زَىْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zihiY","text_ar":"زِهِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; which are likewise said on an occasion of wonder."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iz~aAYo","text_ar":"اـِزَّاىْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iz~aY~","text_ar":"اـِزَّىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iz~aYo","text_ar":"اـِزَّىْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a","text_ar":"اَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i","text_ar":"اـِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", are also said by the vulgar in Egypt on an occasion of wonder, and of denial, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How?"},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaYo","text_ar":"زَىْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used by them for the prefix"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka","text_ar":"كَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Like."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["TA","Kr","S","K","MF"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}